cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a machine learning approach to learn the winning price distribution accurately and devise an optimal bidding strategy. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper deals with real-time bidding, which is a subfield of information retrieval. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a fully parametric censored regression approach and a mixture density censored network, which are both related to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with programmatic advertising, which involves multiple agents (advertisers, demand-side platforms, etc.) interacting with each other. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an AI-based approach to optimize bidding strategy in programmatic advertising.
